Women with the BRCA1 gene mutation have a 50 to 80 per cent risk of developing breast cancer in their lifetime . 
  Carriers of the gene can reduce their risk of death by having their ovaries removed . 
  Angelina Jolie had an oophorectomy after she was diagnosed with breast cancer . 
  The procedure cuts the risk of dying from the disease by more than 60 per cent . 
 